cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of conditional generative models for classification tasks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the issue of adversarial examples, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes methods to improve the performance of conditional generative models, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
